cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM 

The paper deals with video captioning, which involves both computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also introduces a novel key-addressing mechanism for sequence-to-sequence models, which falls under the sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language). The use of deep neural networks with external memory components also falls under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper deals with multimodal data (video and language), which falls under the sub-category of cs.MM (Multimedia).
